This paper is primarily focused on capacity control and regularization of neural networks, which falls under the category of machine learning (cs.LG) and neural networks (cs.NE). The experiments conducted in the paper are primarily on image classification datasets, which suggests that computer vision (cs.CV) could also be a relevant sub-category. The paper also discusses the generalization behavior of ReLU networks, which is a topic of interest in artificial intelligence (cs.AI) research. Finally, the paper proposes a new norm for measuring capacity, which could be relevant to the sub-category of data structures (cs.DS).
